This is a trivial shell example.

Module using type shell will recieve their formal parameter as long style arguments.

For example:
<module type="shell" name="ShExample" codeurl="./list_arguments">
  <tag name="formal-input" value="$client_server" index="0" />
  <tag name="formal-input" value="$image_url:string" index="1" />
  <tag name="formal-input" value="ThresholdValue:number='50'" index="2" />
  <tag name="formal-output" value="resources:string" />
</module>



When executed the script './list_arguments' will be executed with 

./list_arguments --client_server="http://somespot.org/bisquik" --image_url="http://somespot.org/ds/images/<NUM>" --ThresholdValue="<param>" 


NOTE: output parameters are currently ignored.

